# errore convention

This codebase uses [errore.org](https://errore.org/) — errors as union values, not thrown exceptions.

**Before editing TypeScript, read:** `.agents/skills/errore/SKILL.md`

## Quick rules

- Return `Error | T` (or `Promise<Error | T>`) for fallible functions — never throw expected failures
- Check with `if (x instanceof Error) return x` before using the value
- Async boundaries: `.catch((e) => new DomainError({ cause: e }))` — wrap in tagged errors, always pass `cause`
- Sync boundaries: `errore.try({ try: () => ..., catch: (e) => new DomainError({ cause: e }) })`
- No try/catch for control flow; use `import * as errore from "errore"` (namespace import)
- Explicit discard only: `void fnThatMayError()` — lintcn `no-unhandled-error` flags discarded Error unions

## Lint

```bash
mise exec -- bun run lint        # eslint + lintcn
mise exec -- bun run lint:types  # lintcn only (Go rule)
```
